economy is is not very helpful and perhaps even&nbsp;
somewhat damaging so a recession is very narrowly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:52.480
defined it's a technical economic phenomenon&nbsp;
which means two consecutive quarters of negative&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:52.480 --> 00:01:00.360
economic growth um for this reason I think it's a&nbsp;
little bit stupid to focus on things like narrowly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:06.360
missing a recession right the first reason is&nbsp;
you could have one quarter of negative growth and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:10.960
one quarter of very slightly positive growth and&nbsp;
officially that means you've missed the recession&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:17.200
it's really the difference between having&nbsp;
-0.1% growth and +0.1% growth&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:21.400
um really in one case you've had a recession&nbsp;
in one case you've missed the recession&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:28.600
and the difference to your life is basically&nbsp;
completely invisible so this focus on whether&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:35.880
we technically get a recession or not is pretty&nbsp;
ridiculous um the second thing is that really

